{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"239fecdb-07d3-41bd-801b-3c5f6fa2cb6f","content":"With .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` has **native MTP support built-in** — you no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`. That property was only needed for .NET 9 SDK to bridge `dotnet test` to MTP.\n\nHere's what to do:\n\n1. **Remove** `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` — it's obsolete on .NET 10.\n2. **Keep** `<EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>` — this still opts your project into the MTP-based MSTest runner.\n\nThe .NET 10 `dotnet test` detects MTP-enabled projects automatically and communicates with them via the new test orchestrator protocol (no VSTest bridge needed).\n\nWant me to update your `.csproj`?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4b0db176-7c02-42f5-83ea-abd115a025c9","outputTokens":210,"requestId":"BC29:18B6D6:1CE0BE3:1FF48BD:69FA90DE"},"id":"93c56592-4e21-4945-874d-789d076a37da","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:52:53.120Z","parentId":"6c3e853b-afea-4c08-8754-a989de6eb013"}
